snippet.textDisplay:
Oooooh, Babish, you're going to catch a lot of flak for this one. The comments are already pouring in.

You've certainly got a lot of things right but there's a lot wrong too and people are going to get touchy about it.

Potatoes are not Irish. They may by synonymous with the Irish stereotype but they aren't Irish.
It's St. Paddy's, not St. Patty's. Patty makes sense in English as the cutesy word for Patrick but it's not right. Patty is a woman's name.
Shepherd's pie isn't Irish, either. It's British.
